data.title: M0006259: Thanatos and Hypnos bringing a dead warrior to the tomb
data.meta_description: Photograph of a lekythos (vessel for storing oil) decorated with an image of Thanatos (Death) and Hypnos (Sleep) bringing a dead warrior to the tomb. The lekythos is held by the British Museum (museum number 1876,0328.1).
